The paper proposes a new activation function for deep learning and evaluates its performance on image classification tasks using fully connected neural networks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper focuses on image classification, which is a common task in computer vision, suggesting that it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the performance of various activation functions, which is relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
